     Introduction

     The Small Business Opportunity Program was created to act as liaison
     between the Department of General Services, Procurement Division and
     certified small business suppliers. Our main objective is to promote
     the use of small businesses within state government using a variety
     of methods. These methods include:
     * Ensuring that small business is appropriately defined and broadly
       accepted.
     * Unification of government entities affecting small business.
     * Recognition by agencies that contract with small business is
       important.
     * Using database technology to track information regarding the use of
       small businesses.
